The paper introduces a new constraint domain for reasoning about data with uncertainty, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of linear computations in the probabilistic domain, which is relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the empirical evaluation of the proposed method involves data analysis and manipulation, which is related to data structures (cs.DS).
